## ✔️ Circuit Breaker

Opt-in per-origin circuit breaker that stops calling an unhealthy origin once it fails repeatedly, and probes it back to health once a cooldown elapses. It is disabled unless you pass `circuitBreaker`.

```ts
await ofetch("http://api.example.com/users", {
  circuitBreaker: true, // use defaults
});

await ofetch("http://api.example.com/users", {
  circuitBreaker: {
    threshold: 5, // consecutive failures before opening (default: 5)
    cooldown: 30_000, // ms before allowing a half-open probe (default: 30000)
    halfOpenMaxRequests: 1, // concurrent probes allowed while half-open (default: 1)
    failureStatusCodes: [408, 409, 425, 429, 500, 502, 503, 504], // statuses counted as failures (default shown)
  },
});
```

The circuit is keyed by the request's URL origin (not path), and is shared between all clients created from the same parent via `.create()`. Once a circuit is open, requests to that origin reject immediately with a `Circuit breaker is open` error without calling the underlying `fetch`.

